# This rules are you are going to avoid to do

- AVOID premature optimization that complicates code
- AVOID inconsistent naming conventions
- AVOID hardcoding values that should be configurable
- AVOID duplicate code across components
- AVOID direct DOM manipulation when using frameworks
- AVOID mixing business logic with UI components
- AVOID unnecessary dependencies
- AVOID global state when possible
- AVOID nested callbacks (use async/await)
- AVOID security vulnerabilities by following OWASP guidelines
- AVOID tight coupling between components
- AVOID magic numbers and strings
- AVOID complex inheritance hierarchies
- AVOID blocking the main thread
- AVOID memory leaks through proper cleanup
- AVOID race conditions in async operations
- AVOID unnecessary API calls
- AVOID storing sensitive data in client-side storage
- AVOID using deprecated APIs and methods
- AVOID non-semantic HTML structures
